30. Authorization: Role-based access control per project [STATUS: COMPLETED]
Depends on: Ticket 29

Context:
Once users exist, we need to control who can do what. Without authorization, any
authenticated user can edit or delete any project. This ticket adds project-level
roles (owner, editor, viewer) so teams can share projects with appropriate access
levels.

Design decisions:
- Three roles: owner (full control + delete project + manage members), editor
  (create/edit/delete nodes, trees, tags, commits), viewer (read-only).
- The user who creates a project is automatically the owner.
- Owners can add other users to the project with a role.
- A user with no role on a project cannot see it in their project list.
- Superuser concept: if only one user exists, they are implicitly owner of
  everything (smooth single-user experience).
- Open mode (no users in DB): no permission checks, everything accessible.

