33. Live presence: Who is active in the tree [STATUS: TODO]
Depends on: Ticket 29

Context:
Users want to see who else is currently looking at or editing the same tree. This
uses a lightweight database heartbeat approach — no WebSockets, no central server.
Each client writes a heartbeat row to a shared table every 30 seconds, and reads
other users' heartbeats during the regular 5-second poll cycle.

Design decisions:
- Heartbeat table in the shared DB. Each client writes its own row.
- Stale threshold: 60 seconds. If last_heartbeat > 60s ago, the session is dead.
- Presence is per-tree: "User A is in tree X, looking at node Y".
- Editing indicator: when a user has a dirty field (typing in assumption, editing
  title), the heartbeat includes the node_id they're editing. Other users see
  "Alice is editing Node 5" as a subtle indicator on the canvas.
- This is approximate and eventually consistent. 30s heartbeat + 5s poll = worst
  case ~35s before you see someone join. Acceptable for a small team.
- Cleanup: a periodic sweep (on each heartbeat write) deletes rows older than
  5 minutes to prevent table bloat.

Phase 1: Backend — Schema

  1a. ActiveSessionRow — schema.py
  - id: String(36), primary key (UUID — one per browser tab)
  - user_id: String(36), FK to users.id (CASCADE), non-nullable
  - user_display_name: String(200), non-nullable (denormalized)
  - tree_id: String(36), FK to trees.id (CASCADE), nullable
  - editing_node_id: String(36), nullable
  - last_heartbeat: DateTime, non-nullable
  - Index: (tree_id, last_heartbeat)

  Files: schema.py

Phase 2: Backend — Repository + Service

  2a. Repository methods
  - upsert_heartbeat(session_id, user_id, user_display_name, tree_id,
    editing_node_id) -> None
    - INSERT or UPDATE the row
    - Also DELETE WHERE last_heartbeat < now() - 5 minutes (cleanup)
  - get_active_sessions(tree_id, stale_threshold_seconds=60)
    -> list[ActiveSession]
    - SELECT WHERE tree_id = ? AND last_heartbeat > now() - threshold
  - remove_session(session_id) -> None (explicit logout/tab close)

  2b. Pydantic models — models/presence.py (NEW)
  - ActiveSession: session_id, user_id, user_display_name, tree_id,
